GLOBAL-AF - Update

Update operation of resource: global-af

global-af_schema

global-afbody object

instance-name: string
in path

ID of instance-name

as: string
in path

ID of as

in path

ID of our-byte-as_as

af-name: string
in path

ID of af-name

BMP-SERVERS - Update

PUT Cisco-IOS-XR-ipv4-bgp-cfg:bmp-servers/

Update operation of resource: bmp-servers

bmp-servers_schema

bmp-serversbody object

Request Content-Types: application/json
Request Example
{
  : {
bmp serversPUTPOSTDELETEGET
    : [
No descriptionPUTPOSTDELETEGET
      {
        : {
Configure Host Name/Address and Port for BMP\nServerPUTPOSTDELETEGET
          
"host": "string", Name of the BMP server(accepts IPv4/IPv6\nAddress format too)

          
"port": "string" Port Number of listening BMP server

        },
        : {
Initial refresh to generate BGP updatesPUTPOSTDELETEGET
          
"delay": "integer", Delay in seconds before sending Refresh\nrequest to Peers
range: "1..3600"
units: "second"
default: "120"

          
"skip": "null", Skip Route Refresh request to Peers

          
"spread": "integer" Spread over which to send initial Refresh\nrequest to Peers
range: "1..3600"

        },
        
"status-report-interval": "integer", Stats reporting period for BMP server
range: "1..3600"
units: "second"

        
"description": "string", String to describe the BMP server
        : {
TOS (Type Of Service)PUTPOSTDELETEGET
          
"type": "string", Set type of service

          
"value": "string" TOS value to set

        },
        
"create": "null", BMP Server Creation

        
"server-id": "integer", BMP Server ID
range: "1..8"

        
"bmptcp-keep-alive": "integer", configure TCP keep alives to be exchanged\nbetween client and server. Default=1000
range: "0..7200"
units: "second"

        
"maximum-buffer-size": "integer", Range in MegaBytes for the maximum buffer size\nof BMP message queue.\nThe maximum buf-size is\n20% and default buf-size is 15% of the\nplatform\nvirtual memory max-limit (aka rlimit)\n. Please run show bgp process\nperformance-statistics\nto see the individual\nvalues. Unit is in Megabytes
range: "1..4294967295"
units: "megabyte"

        
"initial-delay": "integer", Initial connect delay in seconds in sending\nupdates
range: "1..3600"
units: "second"

        
"vrf": "string", VRF for BMP Server

        
"shutdown": "null", Shutdown connection to BMP server

        
"update-source-interface": "string", Select an interface to configure

        
"bmptcp-maximum-segment-size": "integer", configure TCP maximum segment size.\nDefault=16384.
range: "68..10000"
units: "byte"

        
"flapping-delay": "integer" Delay in connecting to BMP Server after a flap\nhad been detected.
range: "60..3600"
units: "second"

      }
    ]
  }
}
200 OK

Successful operation

400 Bad Request

Internal Error

Response Content-Types: application/json
